The latest releases of Google Earth have changed their default settings to have our 3dconnexion devices disabled.

On Windows 7, enable non-mouse controller in 
Tools | Options| Navigation | Non-mouse Controller 
and restart Google Earth.

On Google Earth Pro, enable non-mouse controller in
Navigation | Non-Mouse Controller
and restart Google Earth.

on the MAC OS, enable non-mouse contoller in
Preferences | Navigation | Non-Mouse Controller
and restart Google Earth.

